(AGEN), an immuno-oncology company with a pipeline of immune checkpoint antibodies and cancer vaccines, today announced that the first patient has been dosed in a Phase 1/2 clinical trial of the anti-OX40 agonist antibody INCAGN1949. The trial is being conducted by, and in collaboration with, Incyte Corporation. "We are pleased with the progress of our fruitful alliance with Incyte and also anticipate advancing a number of Agenus programs outside of the Incyte collaboration, such as our PD-1 antagonist, AGEN2034, into clinical development in the coming months," said Garo H. Armen, Ph.D. Chairman and CEO of Agenus.
